The paper deals with the problem of inferring high spatial and spectral resolution images from low-resolution hyperspectral and multispectral images. This problem is closely related to computer vision (cs.CV) and machine learning (cs.LG) as it involves image processing and optimization techniques. The use of regularization techniques and optimization algorithms also suggests that the paper could belong to the information theory (cs.IT) and numerical analysis (cs.NA) sub-categories. Finally, the paper involves matrix manipulation and large-scale computations, which could also make it relevant to the multimedia (cs.MM) sub-category.
